[[Image:SUDOC screenshot 2013.png|thumb|300px|Screenshot from the  ''Système Universitaire de Documentation (Sudoc)'']]
The '''système universitaire de documentation''' or '''SUDOC''' is a system used by the libraries of [[Higher education in France|French universities and higher education establishments]] to identify, track and manage the [[records management|documents]] in their possession. The catalog, which contains more than 8 million references, allows students and researcher to search for bibliographical and location information in over 3,400 documentation centers. It is maintained by the [[Agence bibliographique de l'enseignement supérieur]].

